      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal grid convergence index (GCI) or Richardson extrapolation applied across at least three mesh levels, with discretization uncertainty quantified and reported for all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "A mesh refinement study was conducted using coarse, medium, and fine grids (4.2M, 8.7M, and 16.1M cells respectively). The hemolysis index showed less than 4% variation between the medium and fine meshes, and the fine mesh solution was selected for all production runs. Engineering judgment supports that the spatial discretization is adequate for identifying worst-case hemolysis trends across the five operating points. The study demonstrates practical mesh independence appropriate for the COU.",
      "note": "GCI values were computed for velocity magnitude but not formally reported for the hemolysis scalar transport equation. Richardson extrapolation was not applied to the primary QoI."
